result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Michael P Dunaway

records.addlTxt:
2:00 PM (64-06) Defendant Michael P Dunaway appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney jeramiah maynard in court for Michael P Dunaway.  Attorney J J. Crawford in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Matter was scheduled for a preliminary hearing but the defendant wishes to waive his right to a preliminary hearing.  Response by Counsel and defendant to Court's questions.  Court finds defendant freely, knowingly and voluntarily waives his right to a preliminary hearing and binds the defendant over. 

State is requesting time to set Arraignment Hearing.
Attorney Maynard is requesting defendant to appear via video- Rock County.

Adj. 2:05PM
Arraignment scheduled for November 14, 2022 at 02:00 pm.

records.descr: Waiver of time limits for preliminary hearing

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Michael P Dunaway in court, in custody by phone from Rock Co.  Attorney jeramiah maynard in court for Michael P Dunaway.  Prosecuting attorney J J. Crawford in court for the State of Wisconsin. Court inquired if victim wished to be heard; no statement made. Charges and penalties explained by the court. Rights given and preliminary hearing requested, time period waived. Minutes filed.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for October 28, 2022 at 02:00 pm.

Defendant Michael P Dunaway not in court.  Attorney jeramiah maynard in court for Michael P Dunaway.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin in court by ADA Samuel Berg. Called @ 1:39 p.m. Appearances made. Matter before the Court for adjourned initial appearance on 22CF421 with TR files tracking. Record by Atty. Maynard that the defendant is currently sitting in Rock County Jail on high cash bond. Further record as to his first appearance and asks that matter be set out for two weeks. Defendant will be allowed to call in for next hearing from Rock County Jail. All matters are assigned to Judge Johnson and are set on his calendar as requested. Court in recess.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for October 7, 2022 at 01:15 pm.

Defendant shall not possess or consume alcohol. Defendant shall not drive a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license. Defendant shall not possess or use illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia. Defendant will not possess any firearms, ammunition or other weapons. Defendant will not in any way contact or attempt to contact any victim(s) listed and will avoid their residence/place of employment or any place they are located and will avoid causing any other person, other than defendant's attorney, from doing so on defendant's behalf.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as through the mail, by telephone, by way of electronic device, in person, or through a third party.  VICTIM(S)/RESIDENCE(S): NO CONTACT WITH R.G.B. dob 2-10-1962, D.R.K. DOB 4-29-1955, S.J.B. 6-28-1952, J.E.B. dob 1-06-1962, E.R.F. dob 7-26-1962, & E.M.M. dob 1-17-1942. Defendant shall personally ensure that payments are made under any Order for Income Withholding if the Court appoints an attorney for the defendant.

Defendant Michael P Dunaway in court, in custody via phone from Rock Co. Jail.  Attorney Jason Mitchel Daane in court for Michael P Dunaway.  Prosecuting attorney Vivien L. TenHaken in court for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney Daane has conflict with defendant, SPD to reappoint. Cash bond set. Minutes filed.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for September 19, 2022 at 01:15 pm.
